# TGM Pro – Telegram Growth Manager

TGM Pro is a Windows desktop app that helps you grow and manage Telegram communities.

- Scrape members from target groups/channels  
- Add members using multiple accounts  
- Schedule recurring announcements with a bot  
- Export scraped members and back up all data  

> ⚠ **Requires a license key**  
> You can download and install TGM Pro, but you need a valid license key to actually use it.

---

## 1. Download

1. Go to the **Releases** page of this repository.  
2. Download the latest **`TGM Pro.zip`** asset.

## 2. Install & Run

1. Right-click `TGM Pro.zip` → **Extract All…**.  
2. Open the extracted **`TGM Pro`** folder.  
3. Double-click **`TGM Pro.exe`**.

On first run you may see a Windows SmartScreen warning (see Troubleshooting below).

---

## 3. License & Activation

TGM Pro is a **paid** application.

- A valid **license key** is required to unlock the app.  
- License keys are issued manually by the seller after payment.  
- On first launch, TGM Pro will ask for your license key.  
- Once activated, the license is stored locally on your machine.

### How to get a license key

- Contact: `<your Telegram @handle or email>`  
- Payment: `<your payment link or instructions>`  
- After payment, you will receive a license key to enter on first run.

Replace the placeholders above with your real contact/payment info.

---

## 4. Basic Usage

### 4.1 Add Telegram accounts

1. Open the **Accounts** tab.  
2. Click **Add Account** and enter:  
   - API ID and API Hash (from https://my.telegram.org)  
   - Phone number  
   - Optional **Account Name** (friendly label)  
3. Complete the Telegram login (code + 2FA if any).  
4. When status is **Logged In**, the account is ready.

### 4.2 Configure groups (Settings tab)

1. Set **Source Group / Channel** for scraping members.  
2. Set **Destination Group** for adding members and announcements.  
3. Adjust filters if needed (online only, username only, min/max age).

### 4.3 Scraper

1. Go to the **Scraper** tab.  
2. Ensure at least one account is **Logged In**.  
3. Click **Start** to scrape members from the source group.  
4. When done, members are stored inside TGM Pro for the **Adder** tab.  
5. Use **Export Scraped Members** to save per-group CSV/TXT files.

### 4.4 Adder

1. Go to the **Adder** tab.  
2. Choose between scraped members or a manual/file list.  
3. Configure which accounts to use and limits.  
4. Click **Start** to begin adding members.

### 4.5 Announcer

1. Configure bot token, destination group, text, and interval in **Settings**.  
2. Open the **Announcer** tab.  
3. (Optional) enable **"Keep only the last message"** so old announcements are deleted.  
4. Click **Start Announcer**.

### 4.6 Export & Backup

- **Export Scraped Members** (Scraper tab) → CSV/TXT per group.  
- **File → Export Data** (menu) → ZIP backup of DB, config, and sessions.

